This paper is about learning sparse statistical models with high order feature interactions. The methodology and algorithms presented in the paper are relevant to machine learning and data science, which are covered by the cs.LG and cs.DS categories. The paper also discusses the use of the Apriori algorithm, which is a well-known algorithm in data mining and falls under the purview of cs.AI. The experiments conducted in the paper are on biomedical datasets, which suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the cs.CE category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of Fenchel duality, which is a mathematical concept that is relevant to information theory and optimization, and thus the paper may also be relevant to the cs.IT category.
